sql:
SELECT COUNT(user_id) 
FROM track_likes 
WHERE track_id = (SELECT track_id FROM tracks WHERE title = '<specific track title>');

external_knowledge:
- Performers refer to the artists;
- Tunes refer to the tracks;
- "Played more frequently" implies a higher count of track plays by the specified user;
- User ID 5 is a specific user referenced in the query.

sql:
SELECT 
  (SELECT COUNT(genre_id) FROM genres) AS genre_count,
  (SELECT COUNT(artist_id) FROM artists) AS artist_count;

SELECT tracks.title, genres.genre_name
FROM tracks
INNER JOIN genres ON tracks.genre_id = genres.genre_id;

SELECT t.title, g.genre_name
FROM tracks t
JOIN genres g ON t.genre_id = g.genre_id;
